    <div class="industry-page-content-wrapper">
      <div class="industry-introduction">
        Environmental, Social, and Governance (ESG) factors have become critical considerations for businesses
        worldwide. Companies are increasingly recognizing the importance of sustainability, responsible practices, and
        ethical governance. ESG is no longer a mere buzzword; it&#x27;s a fundamental aspect of corporate strategy.
      </div>
      <div class="industry-benefits-text">BENEFITS</div>
      <div class="industry-benefits-title">The Rise of ESG in the Corporate World</div>
      <div class="industry-benefits-wrapper">
        <div class="indutry-benefits-text-wrapper">
          <div class="industry-benefits-description">
            Companies often struggle to demonstrate their commitment to sustainability and responsible practices in a
            way that is both credible and transparent. This is where blockchain technology comes into play.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="industry-benefits-collection-wrapper">
          <div class="collection-list-wrapper-9 w-dyn-list">
            <div role="list" class="collection-list-6 w-dyn-items">
              <div role="listitem" class="collection-item-8 w-dyn-item">
                <div class="industry-benefit-card">
                  <div class="text-block-27"></div>
                  <div class="text-block-28">Audit Trails</div>
                  <div class="text-block-29">
                    The immutable nature of blockchain allows for transparent and unchangeable audit trails. Companies
                    can easily comply with regulatory requirements and provide evidence for audits or legal inquiries.
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div role="listitem" class="collection-item-8 w-dyn-item">
                <div class="industry-benefit-card">
                  <div class="text-block-27"></div>
                  <div class="text-block-28">ESG Compliance</div>
                  <div class="text-block-29">
                    Blockchain can enable more transparent and verifiable tracking of sustainable and ethical practices.
                    Companies can provide immutable records of their ESG efforts, making compliance easier to track and
                    audit.
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div role="listitem" class="collection-item-8 w-dyn-item">
                <div class="industry-benefit-card">
                  <div class="text-block-27"></div>
                  <div class="text-block-28">Process Digitization</div>
                  <div class="text-block-29">
                    Digitizing processes through blockchain can result in faster, more efficient workflows. The
                    elimination of paper trails and manual entries drastically reduces human errors, saving time and
                    resources while improving accuracy.
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div role="listitem" class="collection-item-8 w-dyn-item">
                <div class="industry-benefit-card">
                  <div class="text-block-27"></div>
                  <div class="text-block-28">Transparency Boost</div>
                  <div class="text-block-29">
                    In a blockchain, all transactions are stored in a public ledger and are visible to all network
                    participants while remaining secure. This heightened level of transparency can reduce fraud and
                    errors, improve audit trails, and streamline dispute resolution.
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
